                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the east base of the central shrine in the Maṅgaḷapurīśvara temple. <hi rend="bold">Rājarājadēva. Year lost.</hi></p>						
                            
                            <p>The regnal year in this inscription is lost. The available details of date, <hi rend="bold">saptami, Thursday, Svāti</hi>, are insufficient to calculate the equivalent.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the sale of land to the god at Tiruchchōpuram as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> by the <hi rend="italic">mahāsabhā</hi> of Tyāgavalli-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Mēlkānāḍu. Among the boundaries of the land is mentioned the name of a watercourse, <hi rend="italic">pālpāñja peruṅgaḻi.</hi></p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
